		<div class="block-contributor-content">
		<div class="block-contributor-bio small">
			<p><strong><span class="smallcaps">Jean Braithwaite</span></strong> teaches English and creative nonfiction at Valdosta State University in Georgia. Her work has appeared in the <em>New York Times</em>, <em>Bayou</em>, and the <em>Mochila Review</em>. She lives in Lake Park, Georgia, where she frequently climbs trees or the playground equipment at the park, as small children gape to see a grown-up play.</p><a href="/contributors/jean-braithwaite" class="block-contributor-link link-alt small">More From This Contributor&nbsp;&#9656;</a>		</div>
